  "prompt": "What do we call Buffalo meat? Is it bacon?",
  "response": "Buffalo meat is commonly referred to as \"bison\" meat, as bison is the animal that is often raised for meat in the United States and Canada. It is not called bacon; bacon specifically refers to the cured meat from the pork belly of pigs. Bison meat can be prepared in various ways, just like beef, and is known for being leaner than traditional beef.",
